@startuml
title casbinjs/react - Initialization Sequence

skinparam shadowing false

actor ReactApp as App
participant "Consumer Fetch Layer" as FetchLayer
participant "External Endpoint" as Endpoint
box "casbinjs/core"
participant "Authorizer" as Authorizer
end box
box "casbinjs/react"
participant "AuthzProvider" as Provider
participant "React Context" as Context
end box
participant "Child Component" as Child

App -> FetchLayer : request authz data
FetchLayer -> Endpoint : fetch AuthorizationPayload
Endpoint --> FetchLayer : AuthorizationPayload

alt app constructs authorizer before render
  FetchLayer -> Authorizer : createAuthorizer(payload)
  FetchLayer --> App : authorizer
  App -> Provider : render with authorizer
else provider receives payload-derived input
  FetchLayer --> App : payload
  App -> Provider : render with payload / config
  Provider -> Authorizer : create / update authorizer
end

Provider -> Context : publish authorizer state
Child -> Context : consume via useAuthz()
Context --> Child : can / canAny / canAll / helpers

note over FetchLayer,Endpoint
API access belongs to the consumer app.
The library only defines the expected input contract.
end note

note over Provider,Context
casbinjs/react supplies React-specific integration.
end note

note over Authorizer
casbinjs/core supplies the vanilla-ready authorizer.
end note
@enduml
